    <h2>What Is A Locking Wheel Nut?</h2>
    <p>Locking wheel nuts are specially designed fasteners used to prevent wheel theft. To remove them, you need a specific key that matches the same pattern as the fastener. Without the key, the wheel nut is much harder to remove.</p>
    <p>However, these days, wheel theft is not a prevalent as it once was, so locking wheel nuts tend to cause more hassle than they prevent. We regularly contend with locking wheel nuts overtightened and rounded by a garage or remove a security bolt after the key has gone missing.</p>
